zboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ss quest</span><hr size=1> The dude who gives the bracer of hammerfall quest also gives out a nice little housecleaning quest.<br><br>There are 4 crystal spiders scattered around ss, kill em, loot the no drop legs, and turn em in for +cov +yelinak (i think there is more, but i dont remember).<br><br>In the past when you attacked a spider, you would agro other stuff in the vicinity (they were on cov faction), which made you be a bit more creative than just smacking it. well, they changed that and now you can just smack em. <br><br>The spiders are in the following locs, and cast invis on themselves shortly after spawning. i havent figured out the respawn time yet.<br><br>1 - in the fountain in the courtyard<br>2 - go to the bank, but dont go in, go to the next door<br>3 - go through false wall to bank, but drop down the shaft on your left<br>4 - i will have to log in to write down directions to get this one, and will edit them in later <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uxorshaik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xorshaik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/5/02 8:07:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ss quest</span><hr size=1> Just some interesting findings as to what it takes to go through the various levels...<br><br>Warmly took around 20 turn-ins of helmets and toes with a few kill faction hits in between to go from the kindly/warmly transition.. This is ballpark, don't have the exact numbers.<br><br>Last night I got Ally from just 1 or 2 kill tags, so I can safely say that I know near exactly when I got Ally. I acquired 3 helms and 2 toes, turned those in.. Faction was just fine for Skyshrine armor turn ins, on the char in question he turned in cleric pants and multied me my monk pants with no problems.<br><br>This cleric also found that on tagging a giant while waiting for a rez, he was MAXED in ally.<br><br>1 of 2 conclusions:<br>1) armor turn-ins are big faction hits<br>2) Ally is a small range of faction <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ugegil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gegil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/5/02 9:37:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> Armor turn ins are huge faction hits..<br>I went from mid Warmly to Max Ally in 2 turn ins. <br><br>How did I do quests at warmly you ask? the now nerfed necklace from Shadowhaven that gave faction..<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uanolisequestris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anolis Equestris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/5/02 3:46:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Around level 40 you can hunt drakkel wolves in GD for some good xp and faction that would probably raise you a few levels by the time you're done.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Been hunting these wolves since level 35.  Some I found to be a bit to much (i.e. if one hits me for 72dmg I FD and let it go).  Usually I never had a problem.  Once I hit 37 it became fairly simple to solo one wolf on half health, bandage up and grab another. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65300" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.bayarea.net/~smithj/anolis.gif" border="0" alt="Your average, ordinary suitcase."></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uzjinaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zjinaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/6/02 9:21:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> Just another note.... The giants with the beards in Kael are heavy hits on Coldain and rather light hits on Skyshrine.  The clean shaven ones are big hits on Skyshrine, none on Coldain.<br><br>Faction hits on bearded...<br>Your faction standing with Kromrif got worse.<br>Your faction standing with Kromzek got worse.<br>Your faction standing with Coldain got better.<br>Your faction standing with Claws of Veeshan got better.<br><br>On clean shaven...<br>Your faction standing with Kromzek got worse.<br>Your faction standing with Kromrif got worse.<br>Your faction standing with King Tormax got worse.<br>Your faction standing with Claws of Veeshan got better.<br><br>S